# ============================================================================================
# BREADTH (Material Request) — a seventh doctype, campaign Wave 1 (docs/plans/2026-07-20-breadth-
# campaign-past-120.md). UNLIKE Purchase Order, Material Request is NOT mechanically identical to
# its predecessors on every axis: it reuses the date_field mechanism (transaction_date, no
# posting_date — the third doctype on that pattern) but forces a genuinely NEW _list_fields branch
# (status present, grand_total absent — a combination neither Journal Entry, which drops both, nor
# Sales/Purchase Order, which carry both, covers) and a genuinely different party_field decision
# (None, not a real header field like every non-JE doctype so far — see erpnext.py's
# SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES comment block for the full source-cited finding: the `customer` field exists
# but is type-gated to material_request_type=="Customer Provided" and forcibly cleared otherwise).
# TestMaterialRequestListTier below is this doctype's dedicated branch coverage (the same role
# TestSalesOrderDateField played for the date_field mechanism); the round-trip class after it
# proves the mechanical wiring holds end to end, matching the shape of TestPurchaseOrderGoverned-
# RoundTrip above.
# ============================================================================================

class TestMaterialRequestListTier(unittest.TestCase):
    """The ONE genuinely new branch Material Request forces (erpnext.py's SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES/
    _list_fields docstrings have the full source-cited finding): status present + grand_total
    absent is a combination no prior doctype exercised, and party_field=None means NO party column
    is spliced at all — unlike Payment Entry's sometimes-blank "party", there is no header field
    here to be blank. These are dispatch-level pins (test_erpnext.py's TestList already pins the
    client-level field-set shape); this class proves the tool layer threads the same config
    through unchanged."""

