# BREADTH (Dunning) — Wave 2, the fourteenth doctype (docs/plans/2026-07-20-breadth-campaign-
# past-120.md), and the FIRST doctype whose native ledger_preview RPC this broker skips outright
# rather than merely annotates. Mechanically, Dunning is byte-for-byte IDENTICAL to Sales Invoice's
# own SUPPORTED_DOCTYPES entry (party_field="customer", submit_via="run_method",
# date_field="posting_date" — TestDunningMechanicalIdentityToSalesInvoice pins this directly). What
# is genuinely new, and CORRECTS the pinned dossier's own hedge ("projected_gl will be empty, same
# as SO/PO/MR"): Dunning has NO make_gl_entries method anywhere in its class hierarchy (it inherits
# AccountsController, never StockController) — confirmed by a full-tree grep of erpnext/ for
# `def make_gl_entries`, which finds it only on StockController and a short closed list of
# individual doctype controllers Dunning shares no ancestry with. ERPNext's own preview RPC would
# call `doc.make_gl_entries()` as a bare method and raise AttributeError on a live bench, so
# plan_submit skips the network call entirely for this doctype — see erpnext.py's own "Breadth
# (Dunning)" module-docstring section for the full source-cited finding.
# ============================================================================================

