# BREADTH (Maintenance Visit) — Wave 4, the thirty-first doctype and ninth row (docs/plans/
# 2026-07-20-breadth-campaign-past-120.md; dossier at docs/plans/dossiers/maintenance_visit.md).
# party_field="customer": a real, required Link (the same static-party shape Installation Note/
# Supplier Scorecard Period established). status present (Draft/Cancelled/Submitted, read_only)
# alongside a SEPARATE completion_status Select (Partially/Fully Completed) and maintenance_type
# (Scheduled/Unscheduled/Breakdown) — both in_list_view and orthogonal to status itself, forcing a
# TWENTY-THIRD _list_fields branch; grand_total confirmed ABSENT. date_field="mntc_date" (Date,
# reqd, default "Today" — the twelfth date-fieldname pattern; mntc_time is a separate Time field,
# named and excluded). Ledger preview UNCALLABLE — the SAME MRO depth Installation Note
# established (MaintenanceVisit -> TransactionBase -> StatusUpdater -> Document). CASCADE LEAF:
# exactly one hit in a full-tree grep, Maintenance Visit's own self-referencing amended_from. TWO
# genuine data-driven risk flags (the Asset-precedent shape): submitting calls
# update_customer_issue(1), directly rewriting any linked Warranty Claim's resolution_date/
# resolved_by/resolution_details/status via a raw db_update() bypass (Warranty Claim is NOT
# submittable — no docstatus lifecycle to bypass, but validate/on_update hooks and version history
# are still skipped); cancelling first runs check_if_last_visit(), a same-doctype PEER ordering
# constraint invisible to this broker's own blast-radius/cascade machinery, disclosed in PROSE ONLY
# (a sibling read this plan cannot perform, the Installation Note validate_serial_no precedent) — a
# dossier correction: the gate matches on prevdoc_docname STRING equality alone, NOT restricted to
# Warranty Claim by schema.
# ============================================================================================

