# 2026-07-20-breadth-campaign-past-120.md; dossier at docs/plans/dossiers/delivery_trip.md).
# party_field=None — company IS present (reqd), NOT companyless. status CONFIRMED REAL (a genuine
# Select, unlike Asset Movement) but maintained entirely by this doctype's own db_set, never
# disclosed as a runtime risk; grand_total CONFIRMED ABSENT with no substitute of any kind.
# date_field="departure_time" — a brand-new FOURTEENTH date-fieldname pattern (sole member, no
# collision), the THIRD Datetime-typed date_field this campaign has found (after Work Order and
# Asset Movement). Ledger preview UNCALLABLE (bare Document, no make_gl_entries anywhere; skip
# tuple 20). THE CENTRAL FINDING: on_cancel's update_delivery_notes(delete=True) force-clears five
# fields on every linked Delivery Note via the SANCTIONED update_after_submit save path (not a
# bypass). THE SHARPEST FINDING, CORRECTED 2026-07-21 by supervisor verification: the collision
# is real but does NOT land on this Delivery Trip's own cancel step (that step natively succeeds
# as a self-unlinking cancel — on_cancel runs before frappe's own back-link check). It lands on
# the DEPENDENT: this broker's OWN cascade order cancels the Delivery Note first, and that raises
# frappe.LinkExistsError at the NOTE step (Delivery Stop.delivery_note is a child-table Link
# frappe's own check_if_doc_is_linked walks) — so this broker currently has NO WORKING CANCEL
# PATH for a submitted Delivery Trip with a submitted note, either through the leaf (refused by
# the blast-radius check) or the cascade (fails at the note step). Cascade: GENUINELY NOT A LEAF
# — Delivery Note's own delivery_trip field is a real, static, submittable Link back in.
