# BREADTH (Asset Value Adjustment) — Wave 5, the thirty-seventh doctype and fifth row (docs/
# plans/2026-07-20-breadth-campaign-past-120.md; dossier at docs/plans/dossiers/
# asset_value_adjustment.md). party_field=None — company IS present (asset_value_adjustment.json
# line 28) but carries no reqd key (the THIRD such row after Purchase Invoice/Quality Inspection,
# never before consequential). status/grand_total CONFIRMED ABSENT; the three real
# in_list_view columns are finance_book/current_asset_value/new_asset_value. date_field="date" —
# REJOINS Project Update's own eleventh date pattern. Ledger preview UNCALLABLE (bare Document,
# skip tuple 21) — but unlike every other UNCALLABLE row, this document's OWN empty preview does
# NOT mean nothing posts: on_submit synchronously builds AND SUBMITS a sibling Journal Entry
# (the revaluation entry, name written back via db_set before on_submit returns) — the campaign's
# FIRST sibling-document FACTORY. on_cancel cancels that JE via a NEW PERMISSION-ONLY bypass
# grade (ignore_permissions=True short-circuits has_permission for ANY permtype; every hook,
# validation, and version-history check on the JE's own full cancel() lifecycle runs normally).
# update_asset() arms a THIRD sibling-document channel (reschedule_depreciation may cancel an
# existing Asset Depreciation Schedule and submit a new one) plus raw db_update/db_set writes on
# the linked Asset. Cascade: a leaf for its own target scans (nothing links IN), but its own
# "asset" field is one of Asset's own 18 edges, so it appears as a DEPENDENT inside an Asset's
# own cascade graph — two directions of one relationship, the Asset Movement precedent.
# ============================================================================================

