# ============================================================================================
# BREADTH (Contract) — the forty-third doctype (docs/plans/dossiers/contract.md +
# contract.verify.md). party_field=None (Dynamic Link pair, party_type/party_name). status
# PRESENT AND DOUBLED (status + fulfilment_status) but a WRITABILITY ILLUSION post-submit —
# before_update_after_submit recomputes both from start_date/end_date/is_signed on every
# subsequent save, discarding a direct write. grand_total ABSENT, no substitute. company
# CONFIRMED ABSENT — the SEVENTH companyless doctype (signed_by_company/signee_company are decoy
# fieldnames, neither is the registry company). date_field="signed_on" (Datetime,
# allow_on_submit=1, genuinely blank-capable — this broker is STRICTER than ERPNext here: a blank
# signed_on discloses at plan and REFUSES at execute). THE SCHEDULER: update_status_for_contracts
# (daily_maintenance) filters is_signed=True AND docstatus=1 EXPLICITLY — the campaign's first
# confirmed SUBMITTED-STATE scheduler mutator. THE STATUS/DOCSTATUS DISCONNECT: "Cancelled" is
# structurally unreachable once a Contract has ever been submitted (on_discard is the only writer,
# hard-guarded to drafts). Ledger preview UNCALLABLE (Contract(Document) directly). Cascade: a
# CASCADE LEAF (only self-referencing amended_from anywhere in either checkout). Whitelist count:
# 0 (not a first).
# ============================================================================================

