# ============================================================================================
# BREADTH (Asset Repair) — the forty-fifth doctype (docs/plans/dossiers/asset_repair.md +
# asset_repair.verify.md). party_field=None (asset is a fixed-asset reference, never a GL party).
# status="repair_status" PRESENT (Pending/Completed/Cancelled); grand_total ABSENT,
# total_repair_cost stand-in. date_field="completion_date" (Datetime, mandatory_depends_on
# repair_status=="Completed" only — genuinely blank-capable on a SUBMITTED Cancelled-status
# document). Ledger preview CALLABLE (the Asset precedent, NOT the skip tuple) — honest-empty per
# TWO independent causes. THE STOCK ENTRY AUTO-SUBMIT: unconditional, no try/except. THE
# ASSET-STATUS SIDE-WRITE: real, ungated by capitalize_repair_cost, but SUBMIT-ONLY — cancel skips
# validate() entirely (frappe's own run_before_save_methods, document.py:1395-1409), a correction
# to the pre-verification addendum's own "fires ... on cancel alike" claim. Cascade: genuinely NOT
# a leaf — Stock Entry.asset_repair is a direct header-level Link on submittable Stock Entry.
# company present but NOT reqd — the FIFTH such row, genuinely consequential under two independent
# conditions (the AVA honesty grade, not Timesheet's zero-consequence one). IS in
# period_closing_doctypes (hooks.py:339) — natively EQUAL, the Asset precedent.
# ============================================================================================

